1
00:00:05,531 --> 00:00:07,161
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:07,231 --> 00:00:08,731
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:10,201 --> 00:00:11,971
(Episode 29)

4
00:00:18,271 --> 00:00:20,841
Eun Bin, what is this?

5
00:00:21,741 --> 00:00:23,741
It was my mom's.

6
00:00:25,081 --> 00:00:26,351
Your stepmom...

7
00:00:28,381 --> 00:00:30,221
Are you saying
she's my birth mother?

8
00:00:31,521 --> 00:00:32,521
Yes.

9
00:00:33,221 --> 00:00:34,421
No way.

10
00:00:35,291 --> 00:00:37,661
I guess that's why
I liked you from the start.

11
00:00:37,961 --> 00:00:42,031
I guess I felt close to you
because you reminded me of my mom.

12
00:00:42,701 --> 00:00:46,301
When I first found out the truth,
I was terrified.

13
00:00:46,371 --> 00:00:50,041
I worried that you'd planned it all
and approached me on purpose.

14
00:00:50,101 --> 00:00:51,341
I was just so terrified.

15
00:00:52,971 --> 00:00:55,481
I swear, I didn't know anything.

16
00:00:56,111 --> 00:00:57,411
How did you...

17
00:00:58,511 --> 00:01:02,181
end up here in Onjeong,
at our house?

18
00:01:03,821 --> 00:01:04,821
I...

19
00:01:06,121 --> 00:01:08,191
I don't know.

20
00:01:09,421 --> 00:01:10,421
It was just...

21
00:01:11,361 --> 00:01:12,691
all a coincidence.

22
00:01:13,091 --> 00:01:14,291
It's not a coincidence.

23
00:01:16,031 --> 00:01:17,401
This is fate.

24
00:01:18,801 --> 00:01:22,301
I just felt I couldn't
stand in the way of family.

25
00:01:22,371 --> 00:01:23,371
Wait.

26
00:01:25,211 --> 00:01:26,571
Hold on.

27
00:01:29,211 --> 00:01:30,311
Just wait.

28
00:01:43,321 --> 00:01:47,561
What have I done? What did I just...

29
00:01:59,541 --> 00:02:01,441
(3H Acupressure Bed)

30
00:02:27,531 --> 00:02:28,571
What are you...

31
00:02:29,371 --> 00:02:31,841
- doing here?
- I saw you coming and going.

32
00:02:32,411 --> 00:02:36,081
I've seen you around.
So I asked the previous owner,

33
00:02:36,341 --> 00:02:37,581
and they said you were taking over.

34
00:02:41,781 --> 00:02:42,881
Why are you here?

35
00:02:43,321 --> 00:02:44,781
I asked you to pretend
you don't know me.

36
00:02:45,221 --> 00:02:46,491
I even gave you money.

37
00:02:51,121 --> 00:02:52,331
I came to give this back.

38
00:02:53,491 --> 00:02:54,661
Why?

39
00:02:59,671 --> 00:03:01,231
I may not have much,

40
00:03:01,831 --> 00:03:03,371
but I've always lived
an honest life.

41
00:03:04,501 --> 00:03:05,511
Hyeon Cheol.

42
00:03:07,671 --> 00:03:08,881
You can't possibly think...

43
00:03:09,341 --> 00:03:11,951
that I'd harass or blackmail you,
can you?

44
00:03:16,551 --> 00:03:19,051
Anyway, I'm glad to see
you're doing well.

45
00:03:19,721 --> 00:03:21,591
I'm genuinely happy for you.

46
00:03:24,421 --> 00:03:25,461
I'll get going.

47
00:03:28,461 --> 00:03:31,061
We probably won't
see each other again,

48
00:03:31,501 --> 00:03:32,531
so don't worry.

49
00:03:38,471 --> 00:03:39,511
Wait...

50
00:03:48,951 --> 00:03:51,121
Take this.

51
00:03:52,451 --> 00:03:53,451
Go...

52
00:03:54,091 --> 00:03:55,461
and get your leg treated.

53
00:03:56,691 --> 00:03:58,461
It's fine. It's nothing serious.

54
00:03:59,791 --> 00:04:00,861
Besides,

55
00:04:03,401 --> 00:04:04,531
if I take this money,

56
00:04:05,331 --> 00:04:07,501
how could I ever face Jong Gil?

57
00:04:11,001 --> 00:04:13,111
Live a good, happy life.

58
00:04:13,941 --> 00:04:16,211
Jong Gil would have wanted that too.

59
00:04:17,511 --> 00:04:18,911
Then...

60
00:04:19,981 --> 00:04:21,981
(Deep-Tissue Acupressure
and Massage for Spinal Muscles)

61
00:04:26,251 --> 00:04:27,621
If you need any help,

62
00:04:28,591 --> 00:04:29,991
call me anytime.

63
00:05:07,631 --> 00:05:11,061
- That part-timer looks familiar.
- Oh, my. But you know,

64
00:05:11,331 --> 00:05:13,401
it's amazing
how much you two look alike.

65
00:05:13,771 --> 00:05:15,101
She must be your daughter.

66
00:05:16,301 --> 00:05:17,641
I get that a lot.

67
00:05:19,371 --> 00:05:20,841
So that's why everyone...

68
00:05:22,381 --> 00:05:24,181
kept saying we look so alike.

69
00:05:25,081 --> 00:05:28,251
What's with the "ma'am?"

70
00:05:28,681 --> 00:05:31,221
Honestly. Goodness,
you're Eun Bin's friend,

71
00:05:31,281 --> 00:05:32,991
so just call me Mom.

72
00:05:34,291 --> 00:05:36,221
Not even knowing
she was my real mother,

73
00:05:38,291 --> 00:05:40,191
I called her Mom.

74
00:05:48,371 --> 00:05:51,641
If this gets out, my mom will be
kicked out of the house.

75
00:06:04,121 --> 00:06:05,221
We should've always
ordered takeout...

76
00:06:05,221 --> 00:06:06,551
instead of making Se Ri
do everything.

77
00:06:07,351 --> 00:06:08,351
I know.

78
00:06:10,791 --> 00:06:12,561
You're not eating.
What's on your mind?

79
00:06:14,691 --> 00:06:15,701
Dad.

80
00:06:16,631 --> 00:06:18,061
Why am I so unpopular?

81
00:06:18,601 --> 00:06:19,671
That's because you're...

82
00:06:20,231 --> 00:06:21,401
unlikable.

83
00:06:22,271 --> 00:06:23,771
I'm being serious right now.

84
00:06:24,601 --> 00:06:26,441
I'm just getting slammed
with hate right now.

85
00:06:27,211 --> 00:06:29,281
At this rate, Gong Jeong Han will be
the only star to come out of this.

86
00:06:30,681 --> 00:06:31,981
So Jeong Han's getting
a good response?

87
00:06:32,281 --> 00:06:33,281
Yes.

88
00:06:33,781 --> 00:06:36,381
That jerk's video
already has 100,000 views.

89
00:06:36,681 --> 00:06:39,521
The comments say,
"He's a true doctor,"

90
00:06:39,521 --> 00:06:40,951
"A national treasure of medicine,"

91
00:06:41,251 --> 00:06:42,921
"His skills and his character
are perfect."

92
00:06:43,791 --> 00:06:46,061
It's just a whole stream
of endless praise.

93
00:06:46,591 --> 00:06:47,961
They're not wrong.

94
00:06:48,931 --> 00:06:49,961
Don't tell me, Dad...

95
00:06:50,701 --> 00:06:52,601
You didn't post a comment
on his video, did you?

96
00:06:53,701 --> 00:06:54,701
Just eat.

97
00:06:55,601 --> 00:06:56,601
So you did.

98
00:06:58,341 --> 00:07:00,271
- You did, didn't you?
- Just eat.

99
00:07:01,041 --> 00:07:03,011
The inflammation isn't too severe,

100
00:07:03,611 --> 00:07:06,111
so take the prescribed medication
and come back in three days.

101
00:07:07,281 --> 00:07:10,351
I'm afraid I can't come back
in three days, Doctor.

102
00:07:10,921 --> 00:07:13,421
Why not?
Do you need a longer prescription?

103
00:07:13,721 --> 00:07:16,521
No. The truth is, Doctor...

104
00:07:16,591 --> 00:07:18,761
I came all the way from Gangneung
to get your autograph.

105
00:07:20,261 --> 00:07:21,291
From Gangneung?

106
00:07:22,531 --> 00:07:24,961
No wonder I didn't recognize you.

107
00:07:25,631 --> 00:07:27,071
Could you please sign this for me?

108
00:07:28,331 --> 00:07:31,841
Of course. Wow,
I can't believe you came this far.

109
00:07:32,871 --> 00:07:34,171
When did you get here?
You startled me.

110
00:07:34,511 --> 00:07:36,711
There you go.

111
00:07:37,541 --> 00:07:40,681
Thank you so much, Doctor.
I'll keep watching your show.

112
00:07:41,581 --> 00:07:43,051
Thank you so much.

113
00:07:43,381 --> 00:07:46,251
Dr. Yang
from the other clinic is here.

114
00:07:46,251 --> 00:07:47,251
You should get his autograph.

115
00:07:47,251 --> 00:07:50,061
- Yes, I'm the...
- No, thank you. I'm good.

116
00:07:54,531 --> 00:07:55,801
What? What do you want?

117
00:07:56,661 --> 00:07:57,801
I'm here to ask you a favor.

118
00:07:58,061 --> 00:07:59,631
A favor? As if.

119
00:07:59,971 --> 00:08:01,031
Hey, Jeong Han.

120
00:08:01,471 --> 00:08:02,941
Let's at least hear him out.

121
00:08:03,371 --> 00:08:04,441
What is it?

122
00:08:05,001 --> 00:08:07,271
Tomorrow, during the shoot
with Councilor Hwang and his wife,

123
00:08:08,411 --> 00:08:09,541
make sure I get more screen time.

124
00:08:09,911 --> 00:08:13,651
What? How am I supposed to do that?
Do I edit the show?

125
00:08:13,651 --> 00:08:16,481
I'll lead the discussion,
so you just need to talk less.

126
00:08:16,651 --> 00:08:18,681
Be quiet. I have patients to see,
so get out of here.

127
00:08:19,551 --> 00:08:21,721
Hey, come on,
I'm seriously asking for your help.

128
00:08:22,491 --> 00:08:24,391
My public image is
in the toilet right now.

129
00:08:24,691 --> 00:08:28,061
People have the wrong idea,
thinking I'm phony and calculating.

130
00:08:28,561 --> 00:08:32,101
Hey, how is that the wrong idea?
That's 100 percent accurate.

131
00:08:34,001 --> 00:08:35,971
- Hey.
- Don't hold me back.

132
00:08:36,441 --> 00:08:37,541
Director Song.

133
00:08:39,111 --> 00:08:40,111
Really?

134
00:08:41,241 --> 00:08:42,941
"Health Tour" wants to have me on?

135
00:08:43,681 --> 00:08:45,911
I see. When?

136
00:08:46,681 --> 00:08:50,481
Okay, got it.
Man, thank you so much.

137
00:08:53,121 --> 00:08:54,121
What was that about?

138
00:08:54,721 --> 00:08:55,891
Did you just get cast for a show?

139
00:08:56,561 --> 00:09:00,291
- Send in the next patient.
- Yes, sir.

140
00:09:01,791 --> 00:09:02,801
Darn it...

141
00:09:03,801 --> 00:09:07,131
Hey, Dong Ik, wait up! Hey!

142
00:09:07,701 --> 00:09:10,271
Man, that guy is unbelievable.

143
00:09:21,551 --> 00:09:23,251
What time is it?

144
00:09:25,921 --> 00:09:28,651
Gosh, time is crawling by.

145
00:09:30,021 --> 00:09:32,661
I wonder if the clinic
is running smoothly.

146
00:09:33,231 --> 00:09:35,131
But it'd be weird
for me to call first.

147
00:09:36,501 --> 00:09:39,201
But how have I not gotten
a single call?

148
00:09:46,671 --> 00:09:47,671
My gosh.

149
00:09:50,111 --> 00:09:51,111
Hello, Mother.

150
00:09:51,311 --> 00:09:54,111
Hi. Have you eaten anything?

151
00:09:54,511 --> 00:09:58,281
Yes, I ate after the furniture
was delivered and set up.

152
00:09:58,951 --> 00:10:00,991
Really? Do you like it?

153
00:10:01,551 --> 00:10:05,191
Yes. It goes well with the decor,
and it's so comfortable. I love it.

154
00:10:05,461 --> 00:10:07,791
I also got the bed set up
in your room.

155
00:10:08,461 --> 00:10:10,161
Great. Thanks for handling that.

156
00:10:10,501 --> 00:10:14,601
Oh, please. It was nothing.
I don't do much around here anyway.

157
00:10:14,731 --> 00:10:17,741
What are you talking about?

158
00:10:17,801 --> 00:10:20,471
Just relax, and don't do a thing.
All right?

159
00:10:21,711 --> 00:10:24,541
I will. Don't you worry
about a thing.

160
00:10:24,641 --> 00:10:26,881
All right, I'll see you later.

161
00:10:26,981 --> 00:10:30,581
Okay. It feels nice
waiting for you to come home.

162
00:10:31,051 --> 00:10:32,081
I know, right?

163
00:10:32,451 --> 00:10:35,021
It gives me something
to look forward to after work.

164
00:10:35,721 --> 00:10:37,461
Okay. See you later, Mother.

165
00:10:44,701 --> 00:10:45,871
What's that noise?

166
00:10:47,271 --> 00:10:49,301
Right. I started the dryer.

167
00:10:55,781 --> 00:10:58,641
All right. It's time to sort...

168
00:11:00,551 --> 00:11:01,911
the laundry.

169
00:11:05,321 --> 00:11:08,121
Oh, no. What do I do?
Why did it shrink so much?

170
00:11:09,491 --> 00:11:13,861
Gosh, Han Seong Mi,
you can't do anything right.

171
00:11:15,901 --> 00:11:17,301
This is Ju Ah's.

172
00:11:17,901 --> 00:11:20,631
Gosh, Ju Ah's going to flip out
when she sees this.

173
00:11:21,131 --> 00:11:22,331
What am I going to do?

174
00:11:25,341 --> 00:11:26,771
What's wrong with these samples?

175
00:11:27,471 --> 00:11:29,511
Gosh, the fit is completely ruined.

176
00:11:29,611 --> 00:11:32,451
I think it's because the fabric
has less tension than we expected.

177
00:11:32,911 --> 00:11:35,881
We can't send this down the runway.
This is driving me nuts.

178
00:11:37,081 --> 00:11:40,251
Hey, should we try to find
some fabric with more body?

179
00:11:40,421 --> 00:11:44,591
But if we start looking now,
will we make it for the show?

180
00:11:44,961 --> 00:11:46,391
We have to do whatever it takes.

181
00:11:46,791 --> 00:11:50,461
Mr. Park, call fabric companies
and find some with good tension.

182
00:11:50,561 --> 00:11:51,561
Okay.

183
00:11:51,631 --> 00:11:55,171
Mr. Choi and Ms. Shin,
please recheck the other materials.

184
00:11:55,471 --> 00:11:58,601
Mr. Jo, contact the agency
and coordinate the model fittings.

185
00:11:58,671 --> 00:12:01,641
- Let's get moving.
- Got it.

186
00:12:08,681 --> 00:12:09,821
Have you seen Director Yang?

187
00:12:10,421 --> 00:12:14,091
What? No, I haven't. Why?

188
00:12:14,391 --> 00:12:18,421
No reason. He took the morning off,
so I thought he'd be in by now.

189
00:12:19,831 --> 00:12:22,391
Well, he's probably in his office.

190
00:12:35,171 --> 00:12:38,211
Then when his one-year contract
is up,

191
00:12:38,311 --> 00:12:39,881
he could actually be fired?

192
00:12:40,411 --> 00:12:43,481
That will be decided by the results
of the upcoming fashion show.

193
00:12:43,481 --> 00:12:47,551
Wow. That's a ton of pressure
on Ms. Gong.

194
00:12:47,751 --> 00:12:49,221
Tell me about it.

195
00:12:49,861 --> 00:12:51,721
Listen, about this...

196
00:12:51,721 --> 00:12:53,691
Let's keep this from Ms. Gong.

197
00:13:20,721 --> 00:13:21,851
So...

198
00:13:22,421 --> 00:13:24,591
she doesn't want to meet me?

199
00:13:25,461 --> 00:13:27,461
It's not that
she doesn't want to see you.

200
00:13:27,661 --> 00:13:30,701
It's just that you both have
new families that you've found,

201
00:13:31,061 --> 00:13:33,931
and she probably thinks that
cherishing those families...

202
00:13:34,271 --> 00:13:36,771
is more important right now.

203
00:14:14,671 --> 00:14:16,041
Where have you been?

204
00:14:18,081 --> 00:14:19,511
I went to the mattress store.

205
00:14:19,881 --> 00:14:23,321
Don't tell me you told Mom.

206
00:14:29,721 --> 00:14:31,621
I'm begging you, Min Seo. Please...

207
00:14:32,261 --> 00:14:35,331
Don't make me regret telling you.
Okay?

208
00:14:39,471 --> 00:14:43,271
I'm so sorry
for hiding the truth from you.

209
00:14:44,401 --> 00:14:48,211
I feared if her real daughter came,
she'd abandon me.

210
00:14:49,411 --> 00:14:52,781
Weren't you angry with her?

211
00:14:53,381 --> 00:14:55,651
You hate people
who abandon their own children.

212
00:14:55,711 --> 00:14:58,551
Especially since
she lied about it...

213
00:14:58,851 --> 00:15:00,491
to become a part of this family.

214
00:15:03,661 --> 00:15:05,561
At first...

215
00:15:06,991 --> 00:15:08,191
I was angry.

216
00:15:09,231 --> 00:15:11,461
But I know my mom...

217
00:15:12,431 --> 00:15:14,401
had a really hard life.

218
00:15:15,401 --> 00:15:19,101
She had no family, no siblings.
She said she was from an orphanage.

219
00:15:19,511 --> 00:15:22,041
She worked at a hair salon,
then entered a pageant,

220
00:15:22,041 --> 00:15:23,511
and that's how she met my dad.

221
00:15:24,581 --> 00:15:28,311
And she knows that
Grandpa, Dad, my brother, and I...

222
00:15:28,381 --> 00:15:31,251
all can't stand people
who abandon their children.

223
00:15:31,521 --> 00:15:33,051
That must be why she hid it.

224
00:15:38,621 --> 00:15:39,731
Well...

225
00:15:44,061 --> 00:15:47,101
I don't know
what her circumstances were,

226
00:15:47,471 --> 00:15:50,871
but she must have given you up
since it was too hard. But still...

227
00:15:51,871 --> 00:15:55,011
If she still has your photos
and your things,

228
00:15:55,711 --> 00:15:58,541
that means
she hasn't forgotten you, right?

229
00:16:00,651 --> 00:16:02,111
My mom...

230
00:16:04,051 --> 00:16:06,751
She loved me
with everything she had.

231
00:16:08,291 --> 00:16:12,261
I gave her such a hard time
and acted out so much,

232
00:16:12,891 --> 00:16:16,561
but she never said one harsh word
and always loved me anyway.

233
00:16:17,961 --> 00:16:19,631
All of that was meant for you.

234
00:16:21,331 --> 00:16:26,111
The love she should've given you...
She gave it to me, so...

235
00:16:30,281 --> 00:16:32,081
I'm so sorry, Min Seo.

236
00:16:33,881 --> 00:16:37,081
I'm so sorry I took all the love
that was meant for you.

237
00:16:39,491 --> 00:16:43,421
She likely did her best for me,
thinking of you the whole time.

238
00:16:43,491 --> 00:16:46,631
So please don't hate our mom. Okay?

239
00:16:47,031 --> 00:16:48,831
I'm begging you.

240
00:16:55,501 --> 00:16:56,501
Thank you.

241
00:16:58,641 --> 00:17:00,411
If I were in your shoes,

242
00:17:01,241 --> 00:17:03,081
I don't think I could've done this.

243
00:17:04,911 --> 00:17:06,111
Okay, I will.

244
00:17:07,251 --> 00:17:11,121
Until I leave, I won't let on
that I know anything.

245
00:17:11,851 --> 00:17:13,891
I'll make sure
neither you nor our mom gets hurt.

246
00:17:15,191 --> 00:17:16,761
I'll just watch from a distance.

247
00:17:27,271 --> 00:17:28,571
Min Seo...

248
00:17:30,341 --> 00:17:31,771
Thank you.

249
00:17:39,711 --> 00:17:42,851
Yes. I'm so sorry about that.
The payment will be sent right away.

250
00:17:42,951 --> 00:17:43,951
Yes, of course.

251
00:17:45,821 --> 00:17:48,651
What are you talking about?
Why can't you order the fabric?

252
00:17:49,121 --> 00:17:52,621
My request for the extra budget
hasn't been approved yet.

253
00:17:52,961 --> 00:17:53,961
What?

254
00:17:55,061 --> 00:17:58,401
Yes. Okay. I'll look into it
and get right back to you.

255
00:17:58,631 --> 00:17:59,971
- Hello, this is Gong Ju Ah.
- Yes.

256
00:18:00,771 --> 00:18:04,201
What? The show is almost here.
How can you back out now?

257
00:18:05,541 --> 00:18:07,111
That can't be right...

258
00:18:07,841 --> 00:18:09,811
Let me look into it
and I'll call you back.

259
00:18:11,381 --> 00:18:12,741
What? What is it? What's wrong now?

260
00:18:13,011 --> 00:18:16,851
Apparently, the opening artist
never got their deposit.

261
00:18:17,121 --> 00:18:19,451
What? That's completely ridiculous.

262
00:18:19,891 --> 00:18:24,521
- Why is the funding frozen?
- Exactly. Let's ask Director Yang.

263
00:18:25,321 --> 00:18:26,391
Ms. Gong.

264
00:18:26,461 --> 00:18:29,061
- Can it wait if it's not urgent?
- It's urgent.

265
00:18:31,201 --> 00:18:34,101
Hey, Ms. Kim, don't you dare.
I'm serious.

266
00:18:34,371 --> 00:18:36,701
What? What is it?

267
00:18:39,571 --> 00:18:40,671
So you're telling me...

268
00:18:40,911 --> 00:18:44,781
Director Yang's long-term contract
is riding on the fashion show.

269
00:18:45,941 --> 00:18:49,651
Well, Director Yang asked me
to keep it a secret.

270
00:18:50,281 --> 00:18:51,681
Unbelievable.

271
00:18:52,021 --> 00:18:53,851
Why are there so many secrets
around here?

272
00:18:54,521 --> 00:18:58,161
If you knew Director Yang's career
was riding on your project,

273
00:18:58,221 --> 00:19:00,061
imagine how much pressure
that would put on you.

274
00:19:00,261 --> 00:19:03,501
Especially with problems popping up
and you being so on edge.

275
00:19:04,561 --> 00:19:09,031
If I thought telling you would help,
don't you think I would've told you?

276
00:19:09,031 --> 00:19:12,471
There's a reason
I didn't say anything.

277
00:19:13,341 --> 00:19:17,141
Now you know, so pretend you don't.
For his sake. Okay?

278
00:19:17,141 --> 00:19:18,581
And don't go picking
another fight with him.

279
00:19:19,681 --> 00:19:21,611
Gosh, seriously.

280
00:19:24,451 --> 00:19:26,921
Tell the press
the separate entry time...

281
00:19:26,921 --> 00:19:28,751
and the photography guidelines.

282
00:19:29,291 --> 00:19:32,221
And give the family tickets to me.

283
00:19:33,261 --> 00:19:34,261
Okay.

284
00:19:36,431 --> 00:19:37,831
Did you solve the issue
with the samples?

285
00:19:38,331 --> 00:19:40,901
Yes, I found a workaround,

286
00:19:41,171 --> 00:19:43,801
but I'm still waiting
on budget approval.

287
00:19:46,101 --> 00:19:49,371
That's strange.
We still have plenty in the budget.

288
00:19:50,341 --> 00:19:54,551
I also heard the artist's deposit
hasn't been paid.

289
00:19:58,181 --> 00:20:00,551
I'll look into it.
There must have been a mistake.

290
00:20:01,791 --> 00:20:04,791
I'm stopping by the artist's office
on my way out.

291
00:20:06,561 --> 00:20:08,191
- I'm heading out.
- Okay.

292
00:20:18,671 --> 00:20:20,671
(Taehan Group)

293
00:20:23,781 --> 00:20:26,581
Director Baek has lost his mind.
Is he going senile?

294
00:20:26,881 --> 00:20:29,581
Why else would he suddenly order
budget cuts for the fashion show?

295
00:20:29,651 --> 00:20:30,881
Calm down.

296
00:20:31,181 --> 00:20:35,291
- Getting angry won't help.
- Seriously, this is making me mad.

297
00:20:36,191 --> 00:20:40,831
He's staking my long-term contract
with this show's outcome,

298
00:20:41,191 --> 00:20:42,891
and then he went
and froze the budget.

299
00:20:44,561 --> 00:20:46,031
Isn't it obvious
what he's trying to do?

300
00:20:46,531 --> 00:20:49,431
He's dead set on getting
Pacu Nacho away from me.

301
00:20:49,671 --> 00:20:52,041
I've been expecting this
ever since I came to Korea.

302
00:20:53,411 --> 00:20:57,441
Director Baek won't get his way.
Not on my watch. I have a last card.

303
00:20:57,741 --> 00:21:00,051
What?
You're going to tell the Chairman?

304
00:21:00,411 --> 00:21:03,251
No, don't.
It'll just make his condition worse.

305
00:21:03,321 --> 00:21:04,321
Don't tell him.

306
00:21:04,381 --> 00:21:06,651
Then what?
Do you have a better idea?

307
00:21:08,821 --> 00:21:09,861
I should...

308
00:21:10,891 --> 00:21:11,921
find a solution, no matter what.

309
00:21:23,371 --> 00:21:25,841
Wow, this is
a full-on Mediterranean meal.

310
00:21:26,411 --> 00:21:28,541
Yes, Jeong Han made all of this.

311
00:21:28,811 --> 00:21:32,141
- Oh, my, you did?
- Hey, come on...

312
00:21:32,241 --> 00:21:35,781
What? You said she already
found out. What's to hide?

313
00:21:36,181 --> 00:21:39,051
My goodness. Wonders never cease.

314
00:21:40,291 --> 00:21:43,361
Oh, but why are there
only three settings?

315
00:21:43,521 --> 00:21:45,261
That's because I have
a work dinner tonight.

316
00:21:45,561 --> 00:21:47,191
What work dinner? Without me?

317
00:21:47,191 --> 00:21:48,231
Of course.

318
00:21:48,331 --> 00:21:49,931
You can't have a real company dinner
with the boss around.

319
00:21:51,861 --> 00:21:53,071
- I'm home.
- Ju Ah, welcome home.

320
00:21:53,131 --> 00:21:54,131
Oh, Ju Ah.

321
00:21:54,701 --> 00:21:55,871
- The new dining table is here.
- Yes.

322
00:21:55,931 --> 00:21:57,771
Oh, so it is. It's nice.

323
00:21:58,301 --> 00:21:59,401
I have already eaten.

324
00:22:00,441 --> 00:22:04,711
- Yes, the meeting went well.
- Man, Ju Ah is so busy these days.

325
00:22:05,511 --> 00:22:08,481
She's working on the fashion show
with her mom. Of course, she's busy.

326
00:22:09,081 --> 00:22:11,381
You guys go ahead and eat.
I've got to get going.

327
00:22:12,121 --> 00:22:15,551
You're not going to a work dinner.
You're going on a date, aren't you?

328
00:22:15,621 --> 00:22:17,121
Oh, come on. That's not it.

329
00:22:17,691 --> 00:22:19,891
I promise I'll give you
a foot massage tomorrow.

330
00:22:20,391 --> 00:22:21,431
Don't worry about it.

331
00:22:21,691 --> 00:22:24,101
Don't just think
about taking care of me.

332
00:22:24,101 --> 00:22:25,701
Go enjoy your dating life.

333
00:22:26,571 --> 00:22:29,401
Oh, and from now on,
just use my car.

334
00:22:29,971 --> 00:22:31,841
That way, you can go on dates
out of town.

335
00:22:31,941 --> 00:22:33,941
Oh, yes. That's a great idea.

336
00:22:35,071 --> 00:22:37,741
Thank you, Seong Mi. I'm off!

337
00:22:38,081 --> 00:22:39,211
Here I go! See you!

338
00:22:39,641 --> 00:22:41,711
Oh, that boy. Goodness.

339
00:22:42,451 --> 00:22:44,151
Man, I wonder what she's like.

340
00:22:44,421 --> 00:22:46,451
Mom, don't you know anything
about her?

341
00:22:46,751 --> 00:22:50,621
No. He said he'll introduce us
when the time is right.

342
00:22:51,621 --> 00:22:54,461
I hope he meets someone nice
this time.

343
00:22:56,291 --> 00:22:57,301
I hope so.

344
00:22:58,501 --> 00:22:59,871
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

345
00:23:06,241 --> 00:23:07,441
This looks great. Thank you.

346
00:23:11,241 --> 00:23:12,611
It's hard running this place alone,
isn't it?

347
00:23:12,881 --> 00:23:15,151
I posted a help-wanted ad,
but no one's applied.

348
00:23:16,781 --> 00:23:18,621
Is Eun Bin really quitting?

349
00:23:18,821 --> 00:23:21,421
Yes, she's going to help out
at her mom's store.

350
00:23:24,361 --> 00:23:25,821
Here, have a drink.

351
00:23:29,161 --> 00:23:33,031
- You're spilling. What a waste.
- My bad. Sorry.

352
00:23:33,601 --> 00:23:35,631
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

353
00:23:36,501 --> 00:23:39,771
I thought it was weird
when you suggested a "work dinner,"

354
00:23:40,271 --> 00:23:41,571
but I see now
there was another reason.

355
00:23:41,911 --> 00:23:45,241
You're so perceptive,
so why's your love life such a mess?

356
00:23:45,311 --> 00:23:48,451
Come on!
Whose fault do you think that is?

357
00:23:49,611 --> 00:23:52,281
I was trying to nurse my crush
in secret,

358
00:23:52,651 --> 00:23:55,391
but why did you give him my phone
and blow my cover?

359
00:23:55,821 --> 00:23:57,691
I'll set things up for you again,

360
00:23:58,261 --> 00:23:59,761
so be brave
and give it another shot.

361
00:24:00,531 --> 00:24:01,631
What are you talking about?

362
00:24:05,261 --> 00:24:07,771
- Welcome.
- Hello.

363
00:24:07,831 --> 00:24:09,501
Wow, what's the occasion?
You're treating me to barbecue.

364
00:24:10,041 --> 00:24:11,101
What? My gosh.

365
00:24:12,341 --> 00:24:15,611
- Chief, what are you doing?
- Why do you keep doing this?

366
00:24:15,711 --> 00:24:19,441
- Here for dinner, Chief?
- Yes, we just got off work.

367
00:24:19,511 --> 00:24:23,351
- I'm really craving meat today.
- You're craving meat? I see.

368
00:24:23,481 --> 00:24:26,251
Hold on. Man, what should we do?
The place is packed.

369
00:24:26,321 --> 00:24:28,221
- You can sit here.
- Look at that. Two seats, perfect.

370
00:24:28,291 --> 00:24:29,551
- Sit here.
- No, it's okay.

371
00:24:29,551 --> 00:24:30,791
Goodness, come on.

372
00:24:31,421 --> 00:24:33,531
- Excuse me, here! Dong Suk! No.
- Sit down.

373
00:24:34,091 --> 00:24:36,361
Ma'am, can we get 2 soju glasses?
Just 2, please.

374
00:24:36,361 --> 00:24:37,701
- Woo Jae.
- Yes!

375
00:24:37,761 --> 00:24:40,101
- Wow, this meat looks amazing.
- You were craving meat today?

376
00:24:40,171 --> 00:24:42,971
- Yes. Where are the chopsticks?
- They're right there.

377
00:24:43,031 --> 00:24:45,441
- The chopsticks are...
- Man, talk about perfect timing.

378
00:24:45,871 --> 00:24:47,711
- Okay, here you go, Chief...
- Hello.

379
00:24:59,151 --> 00:25:01,121
Why do you keep following me?

380
00:25:01,391 --> 00:25:03,621
The streets are dangerous at night.

381
00:25:04,121 --> 00:25:06,691
I'm just making sure
you get home safely.

382
00:25:08,231 --> 00:25:09,461
No, thank you.

383
00:25:09,901 --> 00:25:11,101
I insist.

384
00:25:11,361 --> 00:25:13,431
How can I let you walk home alone
when you're this drunk?

385
00:25:13,901 --> 00:25:17,641
I bet your blood alcohol content
right now is at least 0.15.

386
00:25:18,741 --> 00:25:21,011
I don't want you
to see me like this,

387
00:25:21,341 --> 00:25:23,141
so just leave me alone.

388
00:25:23,911 --> 00:25:25,741
Like what?

389
00:25:27,951 --> 00:25:29,611
It's bad enough I got rejected,

390
00:25:30,081 --> 00:25:32,821
and now you know I had a crush
on you. It's so embarrassing!

391
00:25:37,491 --> 00:25:38,491
What?

392
00:25:39,521 --> 00:25:40,831
Are you laughing at me?

393
00:25:41,931 --> 00:25:43,161
I was laughing because
I think it's cute.

394
00:25:44,901 --> 00:25:48,301
If you're not going to ask me out,
why would you say that?

395
00:25:49,631 --> 00:25:50,741
You're just getting my hopes up.

396
00:25:56,611 --> 00:25:57,611
Are you up for it?

397
00:26:01,211 --> 00:26:02,311
Up for what?

398
00:26:04,821 --> 00:26:06,051
Being in a relationship with me.

399
00:26:17,261 --> 00:26:18,261
Gong Ju Ah.

400
00:26:29,511 --> 00:26:30,511
What time is it?

401
00:26:30,781 --> 00:26:33,781
Hey, if you're going to sleep,
do it properly. What is this mess?

402
00:26:34,081 --> 00:26:35,951
I'm not sleeping.
I have to pull an all-nighter.

403
00:26:36,781 --> 00:26:39,551
Why? What are you stuck on
that's making you like this?

404
00:26:39,681 --> 00:26:41,651
Everything's a total mess.

405
00:26:42,021 --> 00:26:45,221
I checked everything beforehand,
but I keep finding mistakes.

406
00:26:45,891 --> 00:26:48,061
Don't beat yourself up over it.
Just get it done.

407
00:26:48,761 --> 00:26:53,101
Self-blame makes you think
a small error is a total failure...

408
00:26:53,101 --> 00:26:54,201
Gosh, please...

409
00:26:54,831 --> 00:26:56,771
No, what I'm trying to say is,

410
00:26:56,941 --> 00:27:01,471
- thinking it'll all go wrong...
- Just get out.

411
00:27:03,411 --> 00:27:06,441
You brat.
I'm just trying to help you.

412
00:27:06,711 --> 00:27:10,021
I'll rest a bit more, then work.
Leave the light on when you go.

413
00:27:20,061 --> 00:27:22,091
This place is a dumpster.
An absolute dumpster.

414
00:27:28,201 --> 00:27:30,241
(Launch show look list)

415
00:27:32,871 --> 00:27:36,171
- Hey.
- Mom? What were you doing in there?

416
00:27:37,041 --> 00:27:38,711
Just giving your sister a snack.

417
00:27:40,251 --> 00:27:41,881
That's a first.

418
00:27:43,181 --> 00:27:45,351
Just back from your part-time job?
You're late.

419
00:27:45,951 --> 00:27:47,691
I still have enough time
to wash up and study.

420
00:27:48,691 --> 00:27:51,721
Don't push yourself too hard.
You shouldn't feel pressured.

421
00:27:52,121 --> 00:27:55,961
That pressure can be a trigger
that brings up anxiety.

422
00:27:56,061 --> 00:27:57,961
Yes, Mom. I'll keep that in mind.

423
00:27:58,361 --> 00:28:02,831
What you need now is to acknowledge
the process, not just the outcome,

424
00:28:02,901 --> 00:28:07,141
and to value the effort itself.
That builds stable self-esteem...

425
00:28:07,141 --> 00:28:11,211
Mom. I'm really okay.
You don't have to worry about me.

426
00:28:12,441 --> 00:28:14,081
I'm going to go shower.
I really stink.

427
00:28:25,691 --> 00:28:27,161
What are you up to? Are you busy?

428
00:28:27,431 --> 00:28:29,361
I've got to take this too.

429
00:28:31,701 --> 00:28:33,471
- I said, what are you doing?
- Hey.

430
00:28:33,801 --> 00:28:38,371
I got an offer to be on a TV show,
so I'm researching for my meeting.

431
00:28:39,441 --> 00:28:42,511
You asked Director Song about it?
What's the show?

432
00:28:43,171 --> 00:28:45,241
It's a show called "Health Tour."

433
00:28:45,541 --> 00:28:48,251
A doctor visits mountain homes.

434
00:28:50,051 --> 00:28:51,281
Do you want some advice?

435
00:28:51,751 --> 00:28:55,821
If you really want to do it right,
my TV experience would help a lot.

436
00:28:55,921 --> 00:28:59,791
My goodness, Dr. Han.
Don't you worry about me.

437
00:28:59,861 --> 00:29:03,961
Just worry about yourself, okay?
I might be too busy for you soon,

438
00:29:04,031 --> 00:29:05,131
so don't get upset.

439
00:29:06,361 --> 00:29:07,731
Man, I missed it.

440
00:29:10,201 --> 00:29:11,501
Hey, this is more fun
than I thought.

441
00:29:14,671 --> 00:29:17,641
I guess
there's nothing for me to do.

442
00:29:19,611 --> 00:29:22,351
I should bring some vitamin C too.
Right, vitamin C...

443
00:29:36,091 --> 00:29:37,101
Ms. Na.

444
00:29:37,431 --> 00:29:40,301
What... Why are you here?

445
00:29:41,101 --> 00:29:42,831
What if my family sees you?

446
00:29:43,741 --> 00:29:46,741
I'm sorry. I was visiting my parents
and wanted to see Ju Ah for a bit.

447
00:29:47,941 --> 00:29:49,511
I heard what happened yesterday.

448
00:29:50,181 --> 00:29:52,241
That your mothers had
another run-in.

449
00:29:53,551 --> 00:29:55,351
I'm really sorry about yesterday.

450
00:29:56,011 --> 00:30:00,081
If people find out you're dating,
yesterday will be child's play.

451
00:30:00,591 --> 00:30:02,891
I'll do whatever it takes
to convince my mother.

452
00:30:02,951 --> 00:30:05,661
No, don't you dare say a word.

453
00:30:06,321 --> 00:30:09,331
My daughter-in-law and my Ju Ah...

454
00:30:09,391 --> 00:30:11,131
I don't want to see
either of them get hurt.

455
00:30:11,661 --> 00:30:12,661
Understand?

456
00:30:13,101 --> 00:30:16,601
Please let me at least try
until the very end, Ms. Na.

457
00:30:19,941 --> 00:30:20,941
From now on,

458
00:30:21,441 --> 00:30:23,371
I'd appreciate it
if you didn't come to our house.

459
00:30:24,111 --> 00:30:27,651
And about caring for Ju Ah's mom
under the excuse she's your model,

460
00:30:27,711 --> 00:30:29,151
don't ever do it again.

461
00:30:58,881 --> 00:31:00,881
The stars are so clear tonight.

462
00:31:01,481 --> 00:31:02,481
Right?

463
00:31:03,211 --> 00:31:06,181
Actually, this is a prime spot
for stargazing.

464
00:31:06,621 --> 00:31:08,551
You can even see shooting stars
here sometimes.

465
00:31:09,251 --> 00:31:10,291
Really?

466
00:31:12,361 --> 00:31:15,631
I'm experiencing so many firsts
thanks to you.

467
00:31:16,231 --> 00:31:18,931
See? That's why I said
we should make a bucket list.

468
00:31:20,331 --> 00:31:21,531
I thought of one thing.

469
00:31:22,801 --> 00:31:23,801
What is it?

470
00:31:24,801 --> 00:31:28,071
Moving out of my family's house
and getting a place with Ji Hu.

471
00:31:28,671 --> 00:31:33,041
I feel bad making Hyun Bin sleep
in my dad's room whenever he visits.

472
00:31:34,451 --> 00:31:38,151
I want to give Ji Hu his own room
before he goes off to college.

473
00:31:41,221 --> 00:31:44,161
In that case,
I'm adding that to my bucket list.

474
00:31:44,961 --> 00:31:49,161
Moving out and living together
with you and Ji Hu.

475
00:31:50,931 --> 00:31:52,361
Oh, you.

476
00:31:54,401 --> 00:31:57,241
Anyway, what have you been carrying
this whole time?

477
00:31:57,341 --> 00:31:58,941
Oh, right. This.

478
00:31:59,241 --> 00:32:02,711
Give this to your sister-in-law.
I brought some beef from my shop.

479
00:32:04,181 --> 00:32:06,241
Hey, you didn't have to
bring anything.

480
00:32:06,511 --> 00:32:09,811
Protein is really important
for anyone who is fighting cancer.

481
00:32:09,911 --> 00:32:12,251
Tell me when it's all gone.
I'll bring you some more.

482
00:32:12,951 --> 00:32:14,291
Thanks, Lettuce.

483
00:32:16,151 --> 00:32:17,861
You're so thoughtful.

484
00:32:19,021 --> 00:32:20,461
On that note,

485
00:32:21,331 --> 00:32:22,791
this weekend...

486
00:32:25,001 --> 00:32:26,231
Shall we go on a trip?

487
00:32:28,031 --> 00:32:29,031
A trip?

488
00:32:29,501 --> 00:32:32,201
Yes, my sister-in-law said
I can start using her car.

489
00:32:34,241 --> 00:32:36,941
Your sister-in-law is sick.
How can you think of a trip now?

490
00:32:37,581 --> 00:32:41,951
She worries I'd neglect
my relationship because she's sick.

491
00:32:42,011 --> 00:32:44,351
She's just that kind of person.

492
00:32:46,381 --> 00:32:48,121
If she knew it was me,

493
00:32:48,791 --> 00:32:50,151
I bet she'd feel differently.

494
00:32:50,621 --> 00:32:52,221
She'd be surprised, sure.

495
00:32:53,461 --> 00:32:55,031
But that wouldn't change anything.

496
00:32:57,331 --> 00:32:59,031
Give me your answer by tomorrow.

497
00:32:59,901 --> 00:33:00,971
Okay?

498
00:33:08,211 --> 00:33:10,311
A trip? What's he thinking?

499
00:33:12,411 --> 00:33:15,181
Hold on. If we go on a trip,

500
00:33:15,551 --> 00:33:17,221
wouldn't we be spending the night?

501
00:33:39,341 --> 00:33:42,511
Dorphini... Can you call 911 for me?

502
00:33:43,641 --> 00:33:44,641
Why?

503
00:33:45,111 --> 00:33:47,451
Because I think my heart's about to
burst into flames.

504
00:33:48,851 --> 00:33:53,151
- I'm so embarrassed, Tamin.
- What's to be embarrassed about?

505
00:33:53,551 --> 00:33:54,821
We're adults.

506
00:33:55,351 --> 00:33:56,721
I don't know.

507
00:33:58,291 --> 00:33:59,291
Dorphini?

508
00:34:07,431 --> 00:34:10,641
- Wait.
- What do you mean, "wait?"

509
00:34:10,971 --> 00:34:11,971
<i>Just wait</i>

510
00:34:14,311 --> 00:34:17,011
I don't know.
My gosh, what am I thinking?

511
00:34:17,341 --> 00:34:19,181
- What don't you know?
- Gosh, you scared me.

512
00:34:19,811 --> 00:34:22,851
What? No, it's nothing.
Nothing at all.

513
00:34:23,051 --> 00:34:24,051
I'm going to bed.

514
00:34:32,121 --> 00:34:33,421
Hey.

515
00:34:33,991 --> 00:34:36,061
Aren't you curious about your dad?

516
00:34:37,031 --> 00:34:38,061
Well...

517
00:34:38,661 --> 00:34:40,101
I think he passed away.

518
00:34:42,871 --> 00:34:47,241
I was at a snack bar with your mom,
and someone recognized her.

519
00:34:48,371 --> 00:34:53,141
If what they said was true,
he died when she was pregnant.

520
00:34:57,421 --> 00:34:59,021
They're running a bit late,
aren't they?

521
00:34:59,921 --> 00:35:02,921
Mom said she gets off work soon.
Dad went to pick her up.

522
00:35:06,421 --> 00:35:09,261
Hey, I'm so nervous.

523
00:35:10,191 --> 00:35:13,461
Listen,
my dad is a very suspicious person.

524
00:35:13,531 --> 00:35:16,701
Until recently, he didn't trust Mom
and would even track her location.

525
00:35:17,601 --> 00:35:19,701
Don't worry. I'll be careful.

526
00:35:21,241 --> 00:35:24,841
Kids, CEO Cha is home from work!

527
00:35:28,551 --> 00:35:29,551
I know, right?

528
00:35:29,851 --> 00:35:32,751
- Why are there two bouquets?
- Your brother stopped by earlier.

529
00:35:32,821 --> 00:35:35,821
I see. Mom,
how was your first day at work?

530
00:35:36,851 --> 00:35:41,291
- She sold two new products.
- Wow, really?

531
00:35:41,791 --> 00:35:45,731
Eun Bin, I was born to be in sales.
You have no idea how much fun I had.

532
00:35:46,361 --> 00:35:47,601
Congratulations.

533
00:35:48,271 --> 00:35:52,001
Thank you. You two must have gone
to so much trouble today.

534
00:35:52,101 --> 00:35:53,401
And I heard you even made dinner.

535
00:35:54,671 --> 00:35:57,611
Wait, but...
Min Seo, are you crying?

536
00:35:58,611 --> 00:35:59,741
Hey, why are you crying?

537
00:36:00,481 --> 00:36:01,811
It's just that...

538
00:36:03,211 --> 00:36:04,751
I'm sorry.

539
00:36:05,621 --> 00:36:07,021
What's wrong? What is it?

540
00:36:07,291 --> 00:36:09,991
- Did you two get in a fight?
- No, it's not that. It's...

541
00:36:10,391 --> 00:36:13,821
It's because Min Seo kept saying
she missed her family all day.

542
00:36:14,031 --> 00:36:16,331
Gosh, we were trying
to make you stay...

543
00:36:16,631 --> 00:36:18,361
when you're so homesick.

544
00:36:18,431 --> 00:36:21,731
Hey, Dad! Why don't we,
as father and daughter,

545
00:36:21,801 --> 00:36:24,001
- have a little heart-to-heart?
- What? Why, all of a sudden?

546
00:36:24,471 --> 00:36:26,441
- Do you need money?
- Always.

547
00:36:27,311 --> 00:36:30,441
Min Seo, sweetie,
why are you crying so sadly?

548
00:36:30,641 --> 00:36:33,481
It's okay. Don't cry.

549
00:36:41,051 --> 00:36:45,761
I must remind you of your mom.
You're still such a kid.

550
00:36:45,821 --> 00:36:48,931
Sweetie, don't cry. Come here.
Come on, what's wrong?

551
00:36:49,391 --> 00:36:50,431
It's okay.

552
00:36:51,701 --> 00:36:52,861
Don't cry.

553
00:36:59,941 --> 00:37:01,871
You're still such a kid.

554
00:37:16,951 --> 00:37:20,091
I know I left it on my desk.
Where could it have gone?

555
00:37:22,231 --> 00:37:23,561
Mom came in here, didn't she?

556
00:37:25,201 --> 00:37:27,201
Mom, when you came
into my room yesterday,

557
00:37:27,201 --> 00:37:28,931
did you throw away
the paper on my desk?

558
00:37:29,371 --> 00:37:32,001
The crumpled piece of paper next to
the tissues with your nosebleed?

559
00:37:32,001 --> 00:37:33,141
Yes, what did you do with it?

560
00:37:33,271 --> 00:37:34,271
I threw it away, of course.

561
00:37:34,341 --> 00:37:38,311
What? Why would you just throw away
my stuff like that? Why?

562
00:37:38,641 --> 00:37:42,611
It was crumpled, so I assumed
you were throwing it away.

563
00:37:42,711 --> 00:37:45,351
If it was important,
you should've cared for it better.

564
00:37:46,121 --> 00:37:48,421
Where did you throw them?
In this trash can here?

565
00:37:48,521 --> 00:37:51,721
No. I already tied up the trash bag
and put it out.

566
00:38:10,741 --> 00:38:11,741
I found it.

567
00:38:12,881 --> 00:38:15,281
Grandma, I'm sorry I got mad at Mom.

568
00:38:16,311 --> 00:38:20,121
I know it's important,
but why are you so on edge?

569
00:38:20,851 --> 00:38:21,851
Is something going on?

570
00:38:23,151 --> 00:38:25,621
If this show goes wrong,
Director Yang...

571
00:38:26,221 --> 00:38:27,861
could get fired.

572
00:38:28,891 --> 00:38:30,931
- What?
- And if that happens,

573
00:38:31,361 --> 00:38:33,261
he'll go back to Argentina.

574
00:38:34,801 --> 00:38:37,001
You'd like that,
wouldn't you, Grandma?

575
00:38:37,541 --> 00:38:38,771
But for me...

576
00:38:40,101 --> 00:38:42,141
I'm terrified we'll break up,
and it'll be my fault.

577
00:38:42,611 --> 00:38:43,941
I'm really terrified.

578
00:38:47,681 --> 00:38:50,881
I'm sorry I can't give up, Grandma.
I was wrong.

579
00:38:52,051 --> 00:38:53,051
But...

580
00:38:53,551 --> 00:38:55,251
Please don't be too hard on me.

581
00:38:56,491 --> 00:38:57,991
Work is already so overwhelming,

582
00:38:58,821 --> 00:39:00,891
and now I'm afraid
you'll grow distant too, Grandma.

583
00:39:01,661 --> 00:39:02,891
I'm having such a hard time.

584
00:39:05,001 --> 00:39:06,831
Grow distant?
Why would I grow distant from you?

585
00:39:07,201 --> 00:39:08,501
Don't be ridiculous.

586
00:39:09,731 --> 00:39:10,901
I'm off.

587
00:39:35,191 --> 00:39:38,101
Don't sigh at the breakfast table.
It's bad luck.

588
00:39:38,431 --> 00:39:39,631
I can't help it. I'm upset.

589
00:39:40,001 --> 00:39:41,671
I'm worried
I'll just fade into obscurity.

590
00:39:42,071 --> 00:39:44,971
Honey,
the show's first episode just aired.

591
00:39:45,041 --> 00:39:47,471
- Don't jump to conclusions.
- Right?

592
00:39:47,771 --> 00:39:49,741
They haven't shown
my true charm yet, right?

593
00:39:49,941 --> 00:39:52,511
Of course.
You're the type who grows on people.

594
00:39:52,581 --> 00:39:54,151
So the response will just get
better and better.

595
00:39:54,211 --> 00:39:57,521
Besides, just nail today's shoot
with Councilor Hwang and his wife.

596
00:39:57,651 --> 00:39:58,651
Right.

597
00:39:59,151 --> 00:40:02,621
I'm focusing on the nomination,
so I need you all to be careful.

598
00:40:02,751 --> 00:40:03,851
What do we need to be careful about?

599
00:40:04,661 --> 00:40:08,691
In politics, every little thing
your family does can be an issue.

600
00:40:09,131 --> 00:40:11,361
Don't even think about littering.
Got it?

601
00:40:12,201 --> 00:40:17,101
It's not just me. Understand?
They'll dig up our family's history.

602
00:40:19,141 --> 00:40:20,171
And honey.

603
00:40:20,501 --> 00:40:21,511
Yes? Me?

604
00:40:22,141 --> 00:40:25,211
- What about the shop for the shoot?
- Oh, we got it.

605
00:40:25,481 --> 00:40:27,141
Min Seo and I
will hold down the fort.

606
00:40:27,611 --> 00:40:30,351
Don't worry about the store.
Just focus on the shoot.

607
00:40:31,151 --> 00:40:32,651
Thanks, girls.

608
00:40:33,421 --> 00:40:35,491
Dong Suk,
you make sure you're ready too.

609
00:40:36,321 --> 00:40:39,991
Got it. I'm nervous about
our store getting so much publicity.

610
00:40:40,831 --> 00:40:44,261
Good things are coming for us,
so let's all do our best.

611
00:40:44,531 --> 00:40:47,161
All right, I love it!
Hey, let's do a group cheer.

612
00:40:47,401 --> 00:40:50,301
On "Go, family," we all cheer,
okay? Ready? Go, family!

613
00:40:50,301 --> 00:40:51,341
Gosh, no.

614
00:40:52,301 --> 00:40:53,401
Go get them, honey!

615
00:40:54,571 --> 00:40:57,211
- Let's have some spirit! Come on!
- Whatever.

616
00:40:59,141 --> 00:41:00,311
Could I get your autograph, please?

617
00:41:00,611 --> 00:41:01,881
- Oh, my. You want my autograph?
- Yes.

618
00:41:02,251 --> 00:41:04,551
- Sure.
- I loved you on the show.

619
00:41:04,621 --> 00:41:08,691
My gosh. How is he so popular?

620
00:41:09,891 --> 00:41:11,861
- Thank you.
- The camera loves you.

621
00:41:11,921 --> 00:41:13,321
- Of course.
- Can you sign this, please?

622
00:41:13,391 --> 00:41:15,261
- Me too, please!
- Oh, my.

623
00:41:15,331 --> 00:41:16,991
- Yes.
- Yes, of course.

624
00:41:18,801 --> 00:41:19,801
Here, right here.

625
00:41:20,431 --> 00:41:22,671
- Yes. Here you go.
- I'm so hungover.

626
00:41:23,371 --> 00:41:25,401
Goodness, way to go.

627
00:41:25,771 --> 00:41:27,271
Who told you
to drink so much last night?

628
00:41:27,641 --> 00:41:31,341
Tell me about it.
Gosh, you should've stopped me.

629
00:41:32,141 --> 00:41:34,581
At least Officer Jung
took you home, right?

630
00:41:34,911 --> 00:41:37,251
Yes, I think he did, but...

631
00:41:37,681 --> 00:41:41,021
- I can't remember our conversation.
- Oh, for goodness' sake.

632
00:41:42,721 --> 00:41:44,621
What? Why... Why is he here?

633
00:41:45,261 --> 00:41:46,521
Oh, no. Did I hit him last night?

634
00:41:46,621 --> 00:41:49,331
You hit him?
You could get arrested for assault.

635
00:41:49,461 --> 00:41:51,201
- There you are.
- Hello.

636
00:41:54,931 --> 00:41:58,101
What is it?
Did I happen to hit you last night?

637
00:41:58,871 --> 00:42:00,071
Yes, you did.

638
00:42:00,801 --> 00:42:01,811
You hit my heart.

639
00:42:04,211 --> 00:42:05,241
What?

640
00:42:06,381 --> 00:42:07,381
And?

641
00:42:08,151 --> 00:42:12,451
I'll let you off with a warning,
but you're under my heart's watch.

642
00:42:14,321 --> 00:42:15,321
Here, drink this.

643
00:42:17,451 --> 00:42:19,991
And from now on,
under any circumstances...

644
00:42:22,361 --> 00:42:23,761
Fleeing the scene
is no longer an option.

645
00:42:29,131 --> 00:42:30,501
"Fleeing the scene..."

646
00:42:31,101 --> 00:42:32,601
- "is no longer..." Oh, my!
- Gosh, stop!

647
00:42:33,701 --> 00:42:34,711
Oh, man!

648
00:42:34,811 --> 00:42:38,781
Lettuce and... Add the tomatoes.

649
00:42:39,481 --> 00:42:40,481
Next...

650
00:42:42,811 --> 00:42:44,951
Gosh, seriously.

651
00:42:46,451 --> 00:42:49,021
I thought sandwiches were
supposed to be easy to make.

652
00:42:49,091 --> 00:42:51,961
Why are there so many ingredients?
This is so complicated.

653
00:42:52,891 --> 00:42:55,031
Gosh, I give up.

654
00:42:55,461 --> 00:42:57,531
Okay, I'm done with this.
And then...

655
00:42:58,531 --> 00:42:59,531
What's next?

656
00:43:00,901 --> 00:43:02,231
- Hello.
- Hello.

657
00:43:02,231 --> 00:43:03,801
Hello. Hi, there.

658
00:43:04,441 --> 00:43:07,401
My gosh, Dr. Han. Hello.

659
00:43:08,611 --> 00:43:11,511
Oh, it must be your day off.

660
00:43:11,581 --> 00:43:13,681
I almost didn't recognize you
without makeup.

661
00:43:14,681 --> 00:43:15,681
Yes.

662
00:43:15,851 --> 00:43:19,751
Listen, I got a bit carried away
last time,

663
00:43:19,821 --> 00:43:21,251
and I might have been
a little harsh.

664
00:43:22,351 --> 00:43:25,961
If my son were working
as someone's driver,

665
00:43:26,321 --> 00:43:27,621
I'd be pretty upset too.

666
00:43:27,861 --> 00:43:32,061
Right? I knew you'd understand.

667
00:43:32,661 --> 00:43:36,631
And by the way,
if you're in the market for a bed,

668
00:43:37,131 --> 00:43:38,401
please stop by my store.

669
00:43:40,001 --> 00:43:41,011
(Cha Se Ri, Owner)

670
00:43:41,011 --> 00:43:42,871
"Cha Se Ri, Owner?"

671
00:43:44,611 --> 00:43:45,881
Looks like
you've opened your own store.

672
00:43:46,681 --> 00:43:47,681
Congratulations.

673
00:43:48,511 --> 00:43:49,581
Thank you.

674
00:43:49,981 --> 00:43:53,781
Thanks to your advice,
I can finally pursue my dream.

675
00:43:54,821 --> 00:43:55,821
I'll be on my way.

676
00:44:13,541 --> 00:44:14,771
(Pharmacy)

677
00:44:17,611 --> 00:44:18,611
What?

678
00:44:20,611 --> 00:44:22,751
My gosh. Mi Hyang?

679
00:44:26,121 --> 00:44:27,791
Oh, Mi Hyang.

680
00:44:28,351 --> 00:44:29,351
Ms. Na.

681
00:44:29,791 --> 00:44:32,061
Gosh, I've been so scatterbrained.

682
00:44:32,791 --> 00:44:34,791
I saw your missed call,

683
00:44:35,091 --> 00:44:37,761
and I can't believe I'm just now
remembering to call you back.

684
00:44:38,231 --> 00:44:41,101
It's fine.
That happens when you're busy.

685
00:44:41,771 --> 00:44:45,101
Was something wrong?
Why did you call?

686
00:44:45,571 --> 00:44:47,341
It's just that...

687
00:44:48,341 --> 00:44:53,141
After hearing my story,
my sons went to Seongdam,

688
00:44:53,841 --> 00:44:58,081
and someone said they saw
a person who looked like him...

689
00:44:58,081 --> 00:44:59,421
at a tailor shop there.

690
00:45:01,251 --> 00:45:04,461
Oh, really?

691
00:45:05,661 --> 00:45:10,091
And then, it hit me you also have
a tailor shop in Seongdam.

692
00:45:10,391 --> 00:45:12,961
But which tailor shop was it?

693
00:45:13,661 --> 00:45:15,531
There are a few of them.

694
00:45:16,271 --> 00:45:19,001
I'm not sure about that.

695
00:45:19,501 --> 00:45:23,871
But when they went to check,
they were told the person had moved.

696
00:45:26,141 --> 00:45:28,181
I see.

697
00:45:29,751 --> 00:45:31,521
So, then,

698
00:45:31,681 --> 00:45:35,251
did your sons say
they were going to keep looking?

699
00:45:36,691 --> 00:45:38,961
The boys want to, yes.

700
00:45:40,291 --> 00:45:42,231
Right, I see.

701
00:45:43,261 --> 00:45:46,061
Then,
I'll do some looking around myself.

702
00:45:48,071 --> 00:45:51,071
No, really. I want to help.

703
00:45:51,641 --> 00:45:52,641
Yes, okay.

704
00:45:53,371 --> 00:45:54,471
I'll be in touch.

705
00:46:03,281 --> 00:46:04,521
(EM Mobile)

706
00:46:04,521 --> 00:46:05,951
- Welcome.
- Hello.

707
00:46:07,451 --> 00:46:08,451
All right.

708
00:46:08,821 --> 00:46:11,661
Wait, you made this?

709
00:46:12,691 --> 00:46:16,131
I told you to get some rest.
Why go to all this trouble?

710
00:46:16,431 --> 00:46:20,361
I found a good recipe online,
and it was actually pretty easy.

711
00:46:20,961 --> 00:46:24,001
I wasn't too confident though,
so I picked the easiest one.

712
00:46:24,271 --> 00:46:26,901
- Wow, it looks delicious already.
- Yes, it does.

713
00:46:26,971 --> 00:46:29,041
- Thank you for the food, Dr. Han.
- Yes, dig in.

714
00:46:29,141 --> 00:46:30,741
- All right.
- Thank you.

715
00:46:32,441 --> 00:46:34,241
- You should try it too.
- Yes.

716
00:46:38,351 --> 00:46:39,351
How is it?

717
00:46:40,351 --> 00:46:43,891
- Wow!
- Oh, my.

718
00:46:44,791 --> 00:46:46,391
What? Nurse Oh, what's wrong?

719
00:46:48,791 --> 00:46:49,791
Hey!

720
00:46:50,161 --> 00:46:52,231
- Hey!
- Wait, what's going on?

721
00:46:53,161 --> 00:46:56,401
- It's not that bad.
- Oh, no. Does it taste bad?

722
00:46:56,731 --> 00:46:58,771
No, that's not it, Seong Mi.
That's not it at all.

723
00:46:58,841 --> 00:47:01,671
It's because
she drank way too much last night.

724
00:47:01,671 --> 00:47:02,871
She was drinking.
That's what it is. Yes.

725
00:47:02,941 --> 00:47:05,411
Yes. The seasoning is just right.
It's delicious.

726
00:47:05,541 --> 00:47:09,481
Wow, this is so good.
Mind if I have another one?

727
00:47:10,211 --> 00:47:12,621
- Go ahead, help yourself.
- Thank goodness.

728
00:47:13,221 --> 00:47:16,151
Please, everyone, eat up.
I made plenty.

729
00:47:16,921 --> 00:47:18,721
- Wow!
- It's good, isn't it, honey?

730
00:47:18,721 --> 00:47:20,691
Yes! Hold on. I'm getting a text.

731
00:47:26,901 --> 00:47:27,901
What is it?

732
00:47:29,131 --> 00:47:31,171
Who's it from? What does it say?

733
00:47:32,641 --> 00:47:35,571
Dad... It's from Dad.

734
00:47:37,311 --> 00:47:39,681
- What?
- What?

735
00:47:40,281 --> 00:47:41,281
What did he say?

736
00:47:42,211 --> 00:47:43,711
He says he has no intention
of coming back,

737
00:47:44,981 --> 00:47:47,251
so we should stop looking for him.

738
00:47:54,421 --> 00:47:55,791
I can't believe this.

739
00:48:01,631 --> 00:48:03,531
- Is it ringing?
- The phone is turned off...

740
00:48:05,371 --> 00:48:06,371
It's off.

741
00:48:18,851 --> 00:48:20,651
He said not to look for him?

742
00:48:21,251 --> 00:48:22,251
Yes.

743
00:48:23,651 --> 00:48:25,061
Dae Han told me before he left.

744
00:48:39,701 --> 00:48:42,311
Maybe we shouldn't have
looked for him after all.

745
00:48:44,741 --> 00:48:45,741
No.

746
00:48:46,911 --> 00:48:49,281
I've always had
this nagging feeling,

747
00:48:50,351 --> 00:48:52,221
but now that he's told us
to stop looking...

748
00:48:54,151 --> 00:48:55,321
Now, we can just move on.

749
00:49:06,201 --> 00:49:09,831
(Missing Person)

750
00:49:16,341 --> 00:49:20,441
It's a prepaid phone.
Once you text, just turn it off.

751
00:50:08,431 --> 00:50:11,901
(Onjeong OB-GYN Clinic)

752
00:50:29,881 --> 00:50:32,851
A missed pattern inspection ruined
the whole look? Are you serious?

753
00:50:33,121 --> 00:50:37,651
If the other samples are like this,
we're asking for a public disaster.

754
00:50:38,161 --> 00:50:40,091
- We're sorry.
- We're sorry.

755
00:50:41,061 --> 00:50:44,331
We can't even redo it
since new fabric orders are blocked.

756
00:50:44,631 --> 00:50:46,961
So how are you planning to fix this?
How?

757
00:50:47,301 --> 00:50:52,271
I'll go to the sourcing team
and get a list of leftover fabrics.

758
00:50:52,571 --> 00:50:55,941
I'll start by sorting out the looks
we can save with substitute fabrics.

759
00:50:56,871 --> 00:51:00,111
Can everyone please get their heads
in the game?

760
00:51:00,441 --> 00:51:04,211
If this show is a disaster,
I'm not going down alone.

761
00:51:04,281 --> 00:51:05,351
(Fantom Sports)

762
00:51:08,921 --> 00:51:10,121
Gosh, seriously...

763
00:51:16,661 --> 00:51:18,701
I know this is a terrible time,
but...

764
00:51:19,761 --> 00:51:23,331
our request for a budget increase
was rejected.

765
00:51:24,471 --> 00:51:25,471
What?

766
00:51:27,571 --> 00:51:29,711
They told us to cut it by 30 percent
and resubmit.

767
00:51:29,771 --> 00:51:32,681
So we'll have to cut the show?
And cut down on staff?

768
00:51:33,041 --> 00:51:37,081
This is ridiculous.
Aren't they telling us to cancel it?

769
00:51:42,921 --> 00:51:46,091
All right,
resubmit the budget proposal as is.

770
00:51:46,561 --> 00:51:47,821
It'll be approved, no problem.

771
00:51:49,991 --> 00:51:51,461
How are you going to do that,
Director?

772
00:51:51,861 --> 00:51:54,161
Ms. Gong, a word.

773
00:52:00,601 --> 00:52:01,771
Why are you so on edge?

774
00:52:02,441 --> 00:52:04,541
You know stuff like this happens
all the time at work.

775
00:52:05,011 --> 00:52:07,341
It's because we're being stonewalled
at every turn.

776
00:52:08,351 --> 00:52:10,051
Is it because of what you heard?

777
00:52:10,751 --> 00:52:13,721
That my job is on the line
depending on this fashion show?

778
00:52:16,191 --> 00:52:17,191
Yes.

779
00:52:17,821 --> 00:52:19,791
I'm worried if the show fails
because of me,

780
00:52:20,191 --> 00:52:22,791
you'll be forced to leave.

781
00:52:24,831 --> 00:52:26,761
This is exactly why
I didn't tell you.

782
00:52:28,471 --> 00:52:29,471
I know.

783
00:52:32,101 --> 00:52:33,101
Look,

784
00:52:34,401 --> 00:52:37,171
listen to me, Gong Ju Ah.
This show...

785
00:52:37,641 --> 00:52:39,181
can't be about me. Got it?

786
00:52:40,341 --> 00:52:43,711
Just remember why you started
making clothes in the first place.

787
00:52:45,451 --> 00:52:49,621
That feeling...
Making people happy with your work.

788
00:52:50,491 --> 00:52:51,721
Focus only on that.

789
00:52:57,091 --> 00:52:58,091
So...

790
00:52:58,701 --> 00:53:00,061
what's your plan?

791
00:53:00,361 --> 00:53:03,671
Come on. It's me.
Don't you trust me?

792
00:53:05,001 --> 00:53:06,001
I do.

793
00:53:06,371 --> 00:53:07,441
Good.

794
00:53:07,641 --> 00:53:10,841
So, I need you to stop being
Gong Ju Ah, my girlfriend,

795
00:53:11,241 --> 00:53:12,811
and go back to being
the head designer for Taehan...

796
00:53:13,081 --> 00:53:16,111
and the executive director
of this fashion show.

797
00:53:16,851 --> 00:53:17,851
All right?

798
00:53:19,321 --> 00:53:20,321
Yes.

799
00:53:23,151 --> 00:53:25,491
Gosh, where are we going to get
the budget from?

800
00:53:26,621 --> 00:53:29,291
Maybe ask our other affiliates
to sponsor us?

801
00:53:30,761 --> 00:53:31,761
That won't work.

802
00:53:32,661 --> 00:53:34,531
There's no way
Director Baek would approve that.

803
00:53:35,271 --> 00:53:37,971
We can just push it through,
citing group synergy.

804
00:53:38,501 --> 00:53:40,271
You think
I haven't already thought of that?

805
00:53:41,041 --> 00:53:44,741
Then what's the plan?
You bragged you'd get it approved.

806
00:53:45,611 --> 00:53:47,711
The show is soon. What's the plan?
Pay for it yourself?

807
00:53:52,251 --> 00:53:54,151
Let's give Director Baek
what he wants.

808
00:53:55,121 --> 00:53:56,121
What's that supposed to mean?

809
00:53:58,491 --> 00:54:00,091
All I have to do is quit, right?

810
00:54:08,261 --> 00:54:11,071
(3H Acupressure Bed)

811
00:54:11,131 --> 00:54:15,141
I told you to come this evening.
You didn't have to come early.

812
00:54:15,271 --> 00:54:17,911
We just wanted to help you, Mom.

813
00:54:18,271 --> 00:54:19,281
Oh, you.

814
00:54:20,311 --> 00:54:22,551
Isn't she the sweetest,
most considerate kid?

815
00:54:22,911 --> 00:54:24,911
Min Seo, that's enough.
Take a break.

816
00:54:25,221 --> 00:54:26,451
Just a little more.

817
00:54:26,821 --> 00:54:30,591
A clean store is good for our image.
I have to be thorough.

818
00:54:32,921 --> 00:54:33,991
Welcome.

819
00:54:34,321 --> 00:54:36,531
- Right this way, please.
- Welcome.

820
00:54:37,591 --> 00:54:41,831
My daughter's studying for exams,
and her back hurts from sitting.

821
00:54:41,901 --> 00:54:45,101
I see.
This should really help her back.

822
00:54:45,541 --> 00:54:47,571
And if you try it out, you'll see
it's also great for fatigue relief.

823
00:54:48,841 --> 00:54:49,841
How does it feel?

824
00:54:50,971 --> 00:54:54,411
My fatigue is just melting away.
My back feels better too.

825
00:54:54,481 --> 00:54:56,881
Great! So if you just...

826
00:55:05,161 --> 00:55:08,361
Let's be honest. You didn't expect
Dad to come back, did you?

827
00:55:10,391 --> 00:55:11,391
You're right.

828
00:55:12,401 --> 00:55:14,231
Let's just try to forget him
and move on.

829
00:55:15,401 --> 00:55:17,871
Hey, you have that shoot later.
You should try to cheer up.

830
00:55:18,371 --> 00:55:19,371
It's written all over your face.

831
00:55:20,101 --> 00:55:22,411
I was doing this shoot
so Dad would see it.

832
00:55:23,071 --> 00:55:25,011
It's all so pointless. So pointless.

833
00:55:25,981 --> 00:55:26,981
I know.

834
00:55:27,641 --> 00:55:28,881
Your next patient is here.

835
00:55:29,911 --> 00:55:30,911
Okay.

836
00:55:32,221 --> 00:55:33,221
Yes, hello.

837
00:55:33,721 --> 00:55:36,021
Oh, what brings you in today?

838
00:55:36,651 --> 00:55:40,061
I'm a delivery driver and had
a bit of a motorcycle accident.

839
00:55:40,361 --> 00:55:42,561
Oh, dear. When did that happen?

840
00:55:42,961 --> 00:55:44,161
A while ago.

841
00:55:44,891 --> 00:55:48,201
I wanted acupuncture for the pain,
but was told to go to a hospital.

842
00:55:48,401 --> 00:55:50,601
I see. Right this way, please.

843
00:55:50,671 --> 00:55:52,371
Yes, please be careful. Yes.

844
00:55:52,871 --> 00:55:54,171
There's edema, redness...

845
00:55:54,541 --> 00:55:58,341
- Gosh, it hurts.
- Oh, no. Your motion is limited.

846
00:55:58,841 --> 00:55:59,841
Oh, dear.

847
00:56:00,311 --> 00:56:02,511
It looks like you have a fairly
advanced case of osteomyelitis.

848
00:56:02,951 --> 00:56:04,951
This isn't something
we can treat here.

849
00:56:05,151 --> 00:56:08,221
You need to go to a major hospital
for a full workup immediately.

850
00:56:09,291 --> 00:56:11,551
The pain must have been terrible.
Why did you wait so long to come in?

851
00:56:12,861 --> 00:56:14,961
I couldn't afford
to take time off work.

852
00:56:15,661 --> 00:56:17,791
And I don't have insurance either.

853
00:56:18,061 --> 00:56:20,231
Look, I'll write you a referral.

854
00:56:20,501 --> 00:56:22,131
You absolutely have to
go to a major hospital.

855
00:56:22,771 --> 00:56:24,971
This isn't about
the hospital bills right now.

856
00:56:25,271 --> 00:56:26,301
If you leave this untreated,

857
00:56:26,541 --> 00:56:29,071
the tissue could become necrotic.
Do you understand?

858
00:56:39,081 --> 00:56:40,351
- Hey.
- Hi.

859
00:56:42,691 --> 00:56:43,691
Look at you.

860
00:56:44,151 --> 00:56:47,121
I'm worried. I hope
you don't overdo it at the shoot.

861
00:56:47,561 --> 00:56:49,991
I'm a pro. Don't you worry.

862
00:56:51,691 --> 00:56:53,931
I've only been home for two days,

863
00:56:54,231 --> 00:56:57,371
but dressing up to go out...
It's exciting, you know?

864
00:56:58,301 --> 00:57:00,671
Of course.
You've worked your entire life.

865
00:57:00,971 --> 00:57:04,071
It must be hard for you
to be stuck at home all of a sudden.

866
00:57:05,911 --> 00:57:09,111
It just made me realize
that without my title as Dr. Han,

867
00:57:09,411 --> 00:57:13,921
and as just plain Han Seong Mi,
I'm not all that special.

868
00:57:14,681 --> 00:57:19,091
- It's been a real eye-opener.
- Don't be ridiculous.

869
00:57:20,191 --> 00:57:21,261
I'm off.

870
00:57:21,691 --> 00:57:23,791
- Okay, have a good one.
- Okay.

871
00:57:36,941 --> 00:57:39,511
I asked Jeong Han to give me
a bit more screen time,

872
00:57:40,041 --> 00:57:41,311
but they probably won't, right?

873
00:57:42,211 --> 00:57:46,351
It doesn't matter if they don't.
Dr. Gong won't get a word in.

874
00:57:46,451 --> 00:57:48,551
We'll steer the conversation
our way, honey.

875
00:57:49,351 --> 00:57:50,351
Got it.

876
00:57:50,651 --> 00:57:54,161
The meeting today is
about revitalizing the market, so...

877
00:57:54,461 --> 00:57:57,591
I'll be sure to bring up
how I funded the night market.

878
00:57:58,031 --> 00:57:59,061
You got this.

879
00:58:00,331 --> 00:58:01,501
- Hello.
- You made it.

880
00:58:02,001 --> 00:58:03,771
- Thanks for all your hard work.
- Hello.

881
00:58:03,831 --> 00:58:05,371
- Let's have another great shoot.
- For sure.

882
00:58:05,701 --> 00:58:07,901
- Yes, looking forward to it.
- Looking forward to it.

883
00:58:08,541 --> 00:58:10,871
- Shall we get started?
- Have a seat. All right.

884
00:58:18,821 --> 00:58:20,121
Dr. Gong.

885
00:58:20,451 --> 00:58:22,551
The show's been getting
a really great response.

886
00:58:23,821 --> 00:58:26,161
Yes, better than I expected.

887
00:58:27,921 --> 00:58:30,791
But your reception's been lukewarm,
Dr. Yang.

888
00:58:31,331 --> 00:58:33,361
I'm just saving the best for last.

889
00:58:33,931 --> 00:58:36,671
There's no need to get worked up
over every little thing.

890
00:58:37,831 --> 00:58:41,601
He grows on you.
The response will be huge later on.

891
00:58:42,571 --> 00:58:45,411
I'd be wary of excessive optimism.

892
00:58:45,681 --> 00:58:47,781
It can cloud your judgment.

893
00:58:50,551 --> 00:58:53,751
I'll take that pointed advice
to heart.

894
00:58:54,151 --> 00:58:55,721
Let's just wait
until Councilor Hwang arrives.

895
00:58:56,751 --> 00:58:58,551
What's taking him so long?

896
00:58:59,261 --> 00:59:01,421
I just spoke with him.
He said he's almost here.

897
00:59:04,331 --> 00:59:07,361
(Incoming call)

898
00:59:10,701 --> 00:59:11,701
What is it?

899
00:59:12,541 --> 00:59:13,541
Who is it?

900
00:59:13,701 --> 00:59:15,711
It's an unknown number.
Probably spam.

901
00:59:23,811 --> 00:59:26,621
It's me, Hyeon Cheol.
Can we talk for a minute?

902
00:59:26,921 --> 00:59:28,521
I'll come to your store.

903
00:59:31,121 --> 00:59:33,261
Honey, I just need a second.

904
00:59:34,491 --> 00:59:36,431
If it's not important,
call them back later.

905
00:59:36,831 --> 00:59:39,861
- Councilor Hwang is arriving now.
- It'll only take a second.

906
00:59:56,911 --> 00:59:58,051
Hey.

907
01:00:00,081 --> 01:00:01,621
I bet they'll need my help.

908
01:00:01,781 --> 01:00:04,551
Why would they need you
for the shoot? Woo Jae's here.

909
01:00:04,621 --> 01:00:05,721
Woo Jae can handle everything.

910
01:00:06,821 --> 01:00:09,331
Just sit down and get some rest.
Have a seat.

911
01:00:13,431 --> 01:00:14,701
Listen, honey...

912
01:00:15,331 --> 01:00:18,001
- About that trip...
- No.

913
01:00:19,041 --> 01:00:21,141
I won't take no for an answer.

914
01:00:24,341 --> 01:00:27,441
I went to the doctor's today.

915
01:00:29,311 --> 01:00:30,611
To get a refill on my birth control.

916
01:00:33,451 --> 01:00:34,451
Why are you...

917
01:00:35,321 --> 01:00:36,521
telling me that? That's awkward.

918
01:00:37,121 --> 01:00:40,461
But it suddenly made me wonder.

919
01:00:43,261 --> 01:00:44,261
About what?

920
01:00:46,631 --> 01:00:47,631
If I...

921
01:00:48,331 --> 01:00:50,131
could still have a baby.

922
01:00:52,671 --> 01:00:53,701
What?

923
01:00:54,801 --> 01:00:56,911
I know you said you were fine,

924
01:00:57,471 --> 01:01:01,011
but I know how badly
you've always wanted a child.

925
01:01:03,211 --> 01:01:05,011
I told you not to think like that.

926
01:01:06,881 --> 01:01:11,621
You always put me first.
So I wanted to do the same for you.

927
01:01:13,361 --> 01:01:15,261
I had my hormone levels checked,

928
01:01:18,261 --> 01:01:19,401
and they said it's too late.

929
01:01:20,701 --> 01:01:22,431
My levels have dropped,

930
01:01:23,131 --> 01:01:26,501
and they said I'm entering
perimenopause.

931
01:01:28,271 --> 01:01:29,771
Why did you even get tested?

932
01:01:31,611 --> 01:01:32,711
So, were you upset?

933
01:01:33,481 --> 01:01:34,841
Yes. A little.

934
01:01:36,781 --> 01:01:39,151
I guess I really am getting old.

935
01:01:42,421 --> 01:01:44,721
Dong Suk, getting older is
a perfectly natural thing.

936
01:01:45,351 --> 01:01:46,361
Besides,

937
01:01:47,861 --> 01:01:49,391
I'm older than you are.

938
01:01:52,201 --> 01:01:55,201
If I got tested, they might say
it's my fault we can't.

939
01:01:57,971 --> 01:01:59,541
Are you really okay with that?

940
01:02:00,301 --> 01:02:01,341
Of course.

941
01:02:16,351 --> 01:02:17,921
I love your sneakers.

942
01:02:19,721 --> 01:02:22,021
I really like that guy.

943
01:02:22,991 --> 01:02:24,391
My future father-in-law.

944
01:02:29,601 --> 01:02:30,831
(Dad)

945
01:02:31,201 --> 01:02:33,801
What? He's not even
your stepdad yet,

946
01:02:33,901 --> 01:02:35,241
and you have him saved as "Dad?"

947
01:02:35,611 --> 01:02:37,771
No, it's my real dad.

948
01:02:38,071 --> 01:02:39,081
What?

949
01:02:42,211 --> 01:02:43,281
Hi, Dad.

950
01:02:44,181 --> 01:02:45,251
What's up?

951
01:02:47,021 --> 01:02:48,621
This shoot is taking forever.

952
01:02:49,051 --> 01:02:51,691
I know promoting is important,
but my Dorphini must be exhausted.

953
01:02:53,421 --> 01:02:56,131
I wanted to wait
and take you home myself.

954
01:02:57,161 --> 01:03:00,161
It's okay.
My brother and his wife are here.

955
01:03:01,101 --> 01:03:02,571
Call me when you get home.

956
01:03:03,671 --> 01:03:04,671
I'll be waiting.

957
01:03:05,571 --> 01:03:08,271
Don't wait up. Just go to bed, okay?

958
01:03:09,341 --> 01:03:10,341
All right.

959
01:03:26,361 --> 01:03:27,421
What are you doing here?

960
01:03:29,431 --> 01:03:30,431
Honey.

961
01:03:32,031 --> 01:03:33,701
I told you not to call me that.

962
01:03:34,101 --> 01:03:36,171
I have a good reason to now.

963
01:03:36,901 --> 01:03:37,901
What?

964
01:03:39,401 --> 01:03:42,641
I broke up with Ji Hu's dad.

965
01:03:44,041 --> 01:03:45,041
So?

966
01:03:45,981 --> 01:03:47,811
Aren't you curious why?

967
01:03:48,081 --> 01:03:49,081
Not at all.

968
01:03:49,851 --> 01:03:50,851
I'm...

969
01:03:55,351 --> 01:03:56,651
pregnant.

970
01:03:59,091 --> 01:04:00,091
So?

971
01:04:01,621 --> 01:04:02,791
What do you mean, "So?"

972
01:04:03,831 --> 01:04:04,961
This baby...

973
01:04:05,861 --> 01:04:07,401
is yours, honey.

974
01:04:10,201 --> 01:04:12,031
You wanted a baby so badly,

975
01:04:12,801 --> 01:04:15,911
and it looks like the heavens
have granted your wish.

976
01:04:46,671 --> 01:04:49,411
(Recipe For Love)

977
01:04:49,471 --> 01:04:53,341
- Ta-da!
- It's like you read my mind.

978
01:04:54,411 --> 01:04:56,351
- They approved the extra budget.
- Ta-da.

979
01:04:56,611 --> 01:04:58,781
He really is a man of his word.

980
01:04:59,051 --> 01:05:01,151
I confronted Director Baek head-on.

981
01:05:01,651 --> 01:05:03,121
He said he broke up with that woman.

982
01:05:03,291 --> 01:05:06,491
You know how much Dae Han loves kids
and wanted one, right?

983
01:05:08,191 --> 01:05:09,461
Tell her to have the baby.

984
01:05:09,861 --> 01:05:12,761
My morning sickness is terrible.
It must be a boy.

985
01:05:14,901 --> 01:05:16,671
- I trust you. Completely.
- Honey...

986
01:05:16,731 --> 01:05:17,931
That's what scares me even more.

987
01:05:19,206 --> 01:05:21,106
Dramaday.me
